Update this PR now that github-relay's module.nix has been updated to use native Tailscale Funnel instead of tsnsrv.

## Changes needed

### 1. Remove the tsnsrv stub module from flake.nix
Delete this entire block that was added to the classic-laddie nixosSystem modules:
```nix
# Stub: github-relay module references services.tsnsrv for funnel
# support; declare the option so evaluation succeeds even without
# the tsnsrv module imported (funnel is not enabled).
(
  { lib, ... }:
  {
    options.services.tsnsrv = lib.mkOption {
      type = lib.types.submodule {
        options.enable = lib.mkEnableOption "tsnsrv stub";
      };
      default = { };
    };
  }
)
```

### 2. Enable funnel in hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix
Add funnel.enable to the github-relay config:
```nix
services.github-relay = {
  enable = true;
  port = 8077;
  webhookSecretFile = config.age.secrets.github-webhook-secret.path;
  funnel.enable = true;  # ADD THIS
  consumers = { ... };  # keep existing
};
```

### 3. Ensure Tailscale is enabled
Check if services.tailscale.enable = true exists on classic-laddie. If not, add it. Funnel requires Tailscale to be running.

### 4. Update flake.lock to get latest github-relay
Run: nix flake update github-relay
This pulls the version without tsnsrv dependency.

### 5. Fix the klaus consumer URL
The current PR has the URL as http://10.100.0.2:9800/webhook/github. Check if that IP is correct for how klaus runs on this host, or if it should be http://localhost:9800/webhook/github instead.

### 6. Verify
Run: nix flake check or nix build .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run
